Section X CTAN Edition

Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section X CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

xarticle A class that allows use of 7pt, 8pt and 9pt style options.
Not fully compatible with article class though.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
xcomment Allows selected environments to be included/excluded.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
xdvi A dvi previewer for the X Window System.
license: dfsg version: 20 (1999/03/03)
xdvik No caption.
A (now standard) variant of xdvi with recursive searching for font files in subdirectories.
license: unknown version: 20 (1998/04/06)
xfig No caption.
A menu-driven tool that allows the user to draw and manipulate objects interactively in an X window. Generates pictures for PostScript and a variety of other formats (e.g. for inclusion in LaTeX documents). See also transfig
license: unknown version: 3.2.2 (1998/07/08)
xr References to other LaTeX documents.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
xspace Define commands that don't eat spaces.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
xtab Break tables accross pages.
An extended version of supertabular to automatically break tables accross pages.
license: lppl (1998/10/21)
xtcapts Defining language-dependent text macros.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
xtem An X11 TeX menu built on Tcl/Tk.
It provides a simple and comfortable graphical user interface to control file and directory selection, directory creation, vi, emacs, TeX, LaTeX, previewing, etc.
license: gpl version: 6.18 (1999/04/02)
xymtex Typesetting chemical structures.
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
xypic No caption.
A package for typesetting a variety of graphs and diagrams with TeX. Xy-pic works with most formats (including LaTeX, AMS-LaTeX, AMS-TeX, and plain TeX), in particular Xy-pic is provided as a LaTeX2e `supported package'.
license: dfsg version: 3.7 (1998/11/21)
